Overview
--------
The TQMLS1043A SOM is a high-performance computing platform that supports the
QorIQ LS1043A LayerScape Architecture processor.

LS1043A SoC Overview
--------------------
Please refer arch/arm/cpu/armv8/fsl-layerscape/doc/README.soc for LS1043A
SoC overview.

TQMLS1043A board Overview
------------------------
 - SERDES Connections, 4 lanes supporting:
      - PCI Express - 3.0
      - SGMII, SGMII 2.5
      - QSGMII
      - SATA 3.0
      - XFI
 - DDR Controller:
     - 1GB 32bits DDR4 SDRAM. Support rates of up to 1600MT/s
 - USB 3.0:
    - Three high speed USB 3.0 ports
 - SDHC:
    - eMMC memory devices
    - alternative SD slot for SD, SDHC (1x, 4x) on baseboard
 - QSPI:
    - Onboard support for two SPI flash memory devices
 - 4 I2C controllers
 - ARM JTAG support

Note: XFI function depends on correct initialization by U-Boot. It will
not work as expected when booting into an OS kernel directly from SPL
("Falcon Mode").

Memory map from core's view
----------------------------
Start Address    End Address     Description        Size
0x00_0000_0000 - 0x00_000F_FFFF  Secure Boot ROM    1MB
0x00_0100_0000 - 0x00_0FFF_FFFF  CCSRBAR            240MB
0x00_1000_0000 - 0x00_1000_FFFF  OCRAM0             64KB
0x00_1001_0000 - 0x00_1001_FFFF  OCRAM1             64KB
0x00_2000_0000 - 0x00_20FF_FFFF  DCSR               16MB
0x00_8000_0000 - 0x00_FFFF_FFFF  DRAM1              2GB

QSPI flash map:
Start Address    End Address     Description        Size
0x00_4000_0000 - 0x00_400C_FFFF  RCW,PBI + U-Boot   832KB
0x00_400D_0000 - 0x00_400D_FFFF  U-Boot Env         64KB
0x00_400E_0000 - 0x00_400E_FFFF  FMan ucode         64KB
0x00_400F_0000 - 0x00_400F_FFFF  Linux device-tree  64KB
0x00_4010_0000 - 0x00_417F_FFFF  Linux Image        23MB
0x00_4180_0000 - 0x00_43FF_FFFF  Linux UBI rootfs   40MB

Booting Options
---------------
a) QSPI boot
b) SD boot
c) eMMC boot
